<TITLE> Huda, Al Mamun secure 3-month bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 17 (bdnews24.com) - The High Court on Wednesday granted three months' bail to BNP leaders Barrister Nazmul Huda, Hafiz Ibrahim and businessman Giasuddin Al Mamun in three separate graft cases. The same HC bench, of justice Md Arayesuddin and justice Abu Tarique, also ordered the government to return the passport of former state minister for home Lutfuzzaman Babar, recently bailed out. The HC granted bail to Huda in a graft case, in which a trial court sentenced the former minister to 12 years imprisonment. Ibrahim and Al Mamun were granted bail in two separate illegal wealth cases, for which Hafiz was sentenced to 13 years and Mamun to 10 years. bd
